6\r\n• Tyagi NK, Joshi PK, Aggarwal PK, Khatri-Chhetri A. 2014. Institutions and Policies to Scale Out Climate-Smart Agriculture: South-South Exchanges. CCAFS Workshop Report. Copenhagen, Denmark: CGIAR Research Program on Climate Change, Agriculture and Food Security (CCAFS): https://cgspace.cgiar.org/bitstream/handle/10568/41813/Workshop%20Report%20Colombo%202013.pdf \r\n• Sunil Archak, DP Semwal, Sushil Pandey and BS Phogat (2014). Utilization of ex situ collections and climate analogues for enhancing adaptive capacity to climate change: Final Report. National Bureau of Plant Genetic Resources, New Delhi. India. pp. 47. Available online at: http://www.nbpgr.ernet.in:8080/climate/images/NBPGR_CCAFS_report.pdf \r\n\r\nPeer-reviewed articles citing the analogue apporoach:\r\n• Bellard, C., Leclerc, C., Leroy, B., Bakkenes, M., Veloz, S., Thuiller, W. and Courchamp, F. (2014), Vulnerability of biodiversity hotspots to global change. Global Ecology and Biogeography, 23: 1376–1386. doi:10.1111/geb.12228. Available at: http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/geb.12228/abstract\r\n• Bizikova L, Echeverría D, Hammill A. 2014. Systematic review approach to identifying key trends in adaptation governance at the supranational level. CCAFS Working Paper no. 93. Copenhagen, Denmark: CGIAR Research Program on Climate Change, Agriculture and Food Security (CCAFS). Available at:\r\nhttps://cgspace.cgiar.org/bitstream/handle/10568/51831/CCAFS_WP93.pdf \r\n• Jost C, Sebastian L 2014. Workshop on Mapping out a CCAFS R4D Agenda and Strategy for Southeast Asia. CGIAR Research Program on Climate Change, Agriculture and Food Security (CCAFS). Copenhagen, Denmark: https://cgspace.cgiar.org/bitstream/handle/10568/35586/Workshop%20on%20Mapping%20out%20a%20CCAFS%20R4D%20Agenda.pdf \r\n• Nyairo R., Onwonga R. , Cherogony K., Luedeling E. (2014), Applicability of Climate Analogues for Climate Change Adaptation - Planning in Bugabira Commune of Burundi. Published by Canadian Center of Scien